                                <p><strong>Cryptography</strong> is a way and study to secure communication that protects information from unwanted users from access and modification.
                                    Cryptography's primary purpose is to ensure data Confidentiality, Integrity, and Authenticity<strong>(CIA)</strong>. 
                                    It does this by converting the<strong> plaintext</strong> to <strong>ciphertext</strong> using encryption.
                                    Once the data is <strong>encrypted</strong>, it is sent to the receiver, 
                                    and then the receiver<strong> decrypts</strong> it to retrieve the plaintext.
                                    The different types of cryptography used to encrypt data are<strong> symmetric key</strong> cryptography, 
                                    <strong>asymmetric key</strong> cryptography, and <strong> functions</strong>.
                                </p>
                            <a href="https://www.fortinet.com/resources/cyberglossary/what-is-cryptography"/>Detail information on cryptography</a>
